✨
Happy National Dog Day to my 3 furry sons❣️
Dogs are humans in our family and are treated as such.
They are spoiled, pampered, they get groomed and manicured regularly, hot dinner every night, and celebrate their birthdays.
How do you not spoil these wonderful creatures who are nothing but unconditional love 24/7?!?!
If I could take in 1,000 more and give them loving homes, I would, but I think Van would maybe make me sleep outside if I allow one more into our bed LOL 😂 
If you’re on the fence about getting a dog — DO IT!  There are too many in shelters, especially high kill shelters that need loving homes and are desperate to not be euthanized.
I’m such a softy for these furry friends that every time I see a sad puppy post online, I instantly burst into tears and I just wish I could save them all.  Also cry when one of my friend’s dogs gets sick or dies.
And I’m NOT a crier LOL usually a stone cold ice Queen 👸🥶😂
But sad puppy stories just BREAK ME! 😫
Anyways, today I’m celebrating these 3 goonie birds who spend their days constantly chasing each other, wrestling, and their nights snuggling us and snoring.
They are the 3 best friends that anyone could have.
Monstro can open doorknobs, sliding glass door latches, reach anything, and scare the neighbors over the 10 foot backyard fence like Clifford.
Odin can lock himself in any bathroom and then panic, unplug my charges 5x a day by consistently tripping over them, and likes to bark at the water hose because it is definitely an evil killing device.
Puppito can chew any material dog bed, any expensive workout shoe, and through any bone hard as a rock, and also doubles as a nice height foot stool.
But despite their weird qualities, Monstro acts like the most lovable gentle-giant human child, Puppito is partial to McKenna and acts like her little baby, and Odin gets along amazing with everyone and is the most chill dog ever. 99.9% of the time they are so well behaved and angels thankfully at this age.
I love them to pieces and I’m so glad I’m home with them every day because 7-15 human years is just NOT ENOUGH when they give unconditional love and you love them this much. 😭😭
I LOVE YOU MY SWEET BABIES❣️

I received these AHHHMAZINGGG whole-flower hemp CBD products from the beautiful @ashleymariepls6 who is the mompreneur boss of @rise.and.redemption. 💝
Thank you sooo much Ashley❣️
She was kind enough to send me all 3 CBD products to try, & I’ve been loving them all so far, with my favorite being the Serene. 🙌🏻
✨
Many other CBD products are produced from industrial hemp-CBD isolates, which lack essential cannabinoids, terpenes & compounds. These products are manufactured with a proprietary whole-flower fluid-extraction process that preserves the whole plant & all of its benefits. Since hemp-isolate products lack essential compounds, it takes more of them to give a desired result—& they still aren’t as effective as these products, allowing you to use less, buy less frequently, & save money long term. Unlike oil-based CBD products, this whole-flower hemp CBD oil is extracted directly from the cannabis plant. This unique process creates a water-soluble CBD, allowing for better absorption & quicker results.
✨
Ashley is a lot more knowledgeable about these products than I am, since she reps @tranont, but my video goes over the basics of the products for you & shows you how adorable the packaging is too! 😍
✨
Here is what she sent me:
—Süthe: liquid dropper CBD that is water soluble, & can easily be put right on the tongue or into any drink like water or juice. Water compatible Süthe is arguably one of the most absorbable & bioavailable CBDs on the market. You can feel the strong results & difference it makes with only 2 drops. 
—ReLeaf: a minty smelling CBD muscle rub, that works on sore muscles, painful joints, & even hand issues like psoriasis & eczema. In a convenient pump bottle, & includes 8 botanical ingredients, as well as 6 natural moisturizers. Release the pressure of the day with the power of hemp cannabis, wintergreen, camphor, menthol, peppermint, & rosemary.
—Serene: my FAVORITE of the 3 products due to its gorgeous vape-pen look, the fact that I can keep it in my clutch wallet it’s so tiny, & that it still delivers the immediate CBD strong relief being a spray! Serene CBD spray delivers Brizo Pure's whole-flower, water-compatible CBD
CONTINUED⬇️⬇️

✨
Happy Mother’s Day to all the mommies and grandmas out there!
✨
April 2012, I adopted my first dog who will always be my 1st baby, Bull.
June 2012, I graduated college.
September 2012, just 3 months after I graduated, I conceived my first human child lol, my daughter McKenna.
July 2013 I became a mommy.
✨
Thanks to these two precious souls for making me a mommy and teaching me true unconditional love.
Here is our first year together — the 12 months that forever changed my life for the better in every way, shape, and form. ❤️❣️
You two gave/give me strength in absolutely everything I do. You taught me I could do anything and overcome everything. You brought joy to my days and excitement to my nights. I would never choose anything different than the journey we have had. I ride for you. I fight for you. I’d die for you. 
You have taught me strength in every sense of the word. There’s nothing I won’t do for you, there’s no mountain I won’t climb, and no one will ever come between us.
Everything I have, do, and am, is because of you.
I am unstoppable because of you.
I owe it all to you (and God).

You guys, this new book by Blake Sinclair @blake_sinclairauthor is absolutely amazing!  You just HAVE to check it out! 😍
A New Beginning is literally like a holistic health & healing encyclopedia, covering all sorts of amazing alternative modalities.
✨
I am honored and humbled to be featured in this amazing “new holistic healing Bible,” that I know many will find true health & healing in, since it is such a COMPREHENSIVE resource!  Turn to page 353 to read Metaphysical Medium’s section on Protection, where I cover the first Exorcism I ever did, as well as common everyday methods of energetic protection.
✨
I’m proud to call Blake an author & healer whom I greatly respect, a client, & a friend.  Even thought he was/is my client, I see him as an equal - someone I can bounce ideas off of, & share a like-minded passion with for the metaphysical healing world.  Blake is a seasoned author, with this book being the 3rd & final in his trilogy, as well as an ever-expanding lightbeing of spirituality who is always searching for more.  His hunger for knowledge makes him a great resource for alternative healing information, as he has compiled some of the most relevant tidbits from many of the world’s biggest professional healers.
Blake has over 30 years of experience in many different modalities such as Occupational Therapy, Acupressure, Reiki, Hypnosis, Psych-K, neurology, psychology, & spiritual practices like meditation, breath work, & life/mindset coaching.
✨
This book has so many useful tools for health & healing that I know it can benefit just about anyone.  No matter where you are on your healing journey - from beginning to seasoned - you can learn how to achieve true healing in all 4 bodies (mental, emotional, physical, & spiritual) with A New Beginning! 🥰
✨
Purchase Blake’s new book on Amazon, where you can also find the other 2 books in this trilogy.
Or visit his website at www.BlakeSinclair.org 🤗
✨
Thank you Blake for this beautiful book & all your heart-felt contributions to up-leveling humanity & raising the vibration of the planet! ❤️
✨

node.text:
.
✨
Merry Christmas everyone! 🎄🎅🏻⛄️🎁❄️
I hope your day was filled with love & joy, family & friends❣️
✨
Every year I go ALL OUT creating a Winter Wonderland in our home.  Anyone who knows me knows that I’m OBSESSED with decorating for Christmas & making it a magical place for our family to celebrate the birth of Jesus. ✝️
The funny thing is, my sister in Kentucky is equally fanatical about decorating for Christmas, & she actually starts MONTHS ahead of time which totally cracks me up. 🤣
I usually start decorating on the 1st of December, but got started a few days later this year.  Our family tradition going back generations on my Italian father’s side is to leave up our decorations until 1/6 (which is The Epiphany or “La Befana” a national Christmas holiday in Italy) & also happens to be my birthday 🥳🎉🎊🎈🎁 so we have another 2 weeks of enjoying the festive decorations before they come down, which I absolutely love! 😍🥰
✨
Having a space filled with lights, glitter, sentimental trinkets, cards, photos, & memories always gets McKenna & I in the spirit — she looks forward to helping me decorate every year, & this year being 7, had a lot to say about where things should go — so cute!
✨
I hope you all enjoyed your Christmas & you got to nurture the artistic side of your brain by doing a little decorative creating, whether it was your home, your tree, a gingerbread house, candles, or whatever other traditions you enjoy! ❤️
✨

node.text:
.
✨
Happy 3rd Birthday to my baby boy Monstro & 4th Birthday to my big boy Odin 🐶🐶❣️
Born during the month of Christmas, they truly are both a precious gift 💝 
✨
They are best friends, brothers, & inseparable.  I’ve never seen two dogs wrestle 24/7, play all day, & love each other so much.
From the day Monstro came home, he was attached at Odin’s hip, & when he quickly outgrew him, he made sure to be extra gentle with him & never hurt him during their multiple daily hour-long wrestling matches.
They eat together, sleep together, go to the groomers together... you can’t ever find them apart.  Watching their bond grow over the years has been simply amazing, with lots of laughs at their ridiculous play full speed gallops in the backyard & dive bombing each other for fun.
✨
Birthday steak, some candles, & a giant new stuffy made these boys feel extra special & celebrated.
Watch til the end so you can see them passed out after an epic birthday... they both partied too hard.
✨
I’m so grateful to have these two in my life.  Dogs really do show you unconditional love, & anyone who knows me, knows how obsessed I am with them.  They will forever have a special place in my heart as my fur babies.
✨
This is a big year for them, as there have been a lot of changes, & for Christmas they get a new little brother. 🐶
✨

One of my all time favorite books about treating the root cause of illness, written by @drbenlynch 
✨
If you are interested in learning about genetics, naturopathic medicine, holistic health, optimizing your body, or beating chronic illness, this is definitely the book for you! I’ve read this book a few times & I swear every time I do, I learn something new that I missed the previous time. Having gone through his own health challenges, Dr. Lynch discovered that “dirty genes” were the roots cause, & that these genes could be “born dirty,” or based on our poor lifestyle choices - “act dirty.”
✨
There are so many factors that affect our genes’ behavior, & this book walks you through proven plans that Dr. Ben Lynch used to heal himself & thousands of clients by eating healthy, detoxing, & managing stress & sleep.
✨
The book talks about how exactly dirty genes can create a whole host of problems including: Brain & Mood Issues, Cancer, Cardiovascular Issues, Female Hormone Issues, Fertility & Pregnancy Issues, Gland & Organ Issues, & Metabolism Issues.
It also dives deep into the 7 most common & far reaching genes that can be dirty, which Dr. Lynch calls the Super Seven:
-MTHFR: methylation master gene
-COMT: gene that affects mood, focus, & estrogen
-DAO: gene that can make you super sensitive to certain foods & chemicals
-MAOA: gene that affects mood swings & carb cravings
-GST/GPX: gene that can create detox dilemmas
-NOS3: gene that can create heart issues
-PEMT: gene that supports cell membranes & liver
✨
I also love Dr. Lynch’s supplement line @seeking.health. I take their Vit D, Vit C, Zinc Lozenges, HomocysteX, & B12 L-5-MTHF daily.

✨
Happy National Dog Day to my 3 furry sons❣️
Dogs are humans in our family and are treated as such.
They are spoiled, pampered, they get groomed and manicured regularly, hot dinner every night, and celebrate their birthdays.
How do you not spoil these wonderful creatures who are nothing but unconditional love 24/7?!?!
If I could take in 1,000 more and give them loving homes, I would, but I think Van would maybe make me sleep outside if I allow one more into our bed LOL 😂 
If you’re on the fence about getting a dog — DO IT!  There are too many in shelters, especially high kill shelters that need loving homes and are desperate to not be euthanized.
I’m such a softy for these furry friends that every time I see a sad puppy post online, I instantly burst into tears and I just wish I could save them all.  Also cry when one of my friend’s dogs gets sick or dies.
And I’m NOT a crier LOL usually a stone cold ice Queen 👸🥶😂
But sad puppy stories just BREAK ME! 😫
Anyways, today I’m celebrating these 3 goonie birds who spend their days constantly chasing each other, wrestling, and their nights snuggling us and snoring.
They are the 3 best friends that anyone could have.
Monstro can open doorknobs, sliding glass door latches, reach anything, and scare the neighbors over the 10 foot backyard fence like Clifford.
Odin can lock himself in any bathroom and then panic, unplug my charges 5x a day by consistently tripping over them, and likes to bark at the water hose because it is definitely an evil killing device.
Puppito can chew any material dog bed, any expensive workout shoe, and through any bone hard as a rock, and also doubles as a nice height foot stool.
But despite their weird qualities, Monstro acts like the most lovable gentle-giant human child, Puppito is partial to McKenna and acts like her little baby, and Odin gets along amazing with everyone and is the most chill dog ever. 99.9% of the time they are so well behaved and angels thankfully at this age.
I love them to pieces and I’m so glad I’m home with them every day because 7-15 human years is just NOT ENOUGH when they give unconditional love and you love them this much. 😭😭
I LOVE YOU MY SWEET BABIES❣️

node.text:
✨CERTIFIED TRAINER OF NEURO-LINGUISTIC PROGRAMMING✨
✨
I can’t even put into words what this means to me to graduate a program I’ve been working towards since 2017.
✨
There were countless hours of travel, lots of financial investment, more HOURS than I even know to count, more sleep deprived nights than what is probably healthy, pre-requisites, and deep unwavering commitment.
I can honestly say this is the hardest thing I’ve ever done in my entire life…
Harder than childbirth, harder than any course I’ve ever taken, harder than my Bachelors and Masters degrees, harder than single-parenting for years, and harder than 3 life saving surgeries in 3 years as well as battling 2 chronic illnesses into remission.
✨
It’s been 24 hours since I graduated, and I’m still recovering from so much sleep deprivation that it truly hasn’t hit me yet, but the excitement and gratitude is starting to hit me in waves.
✨
I definitely couldn’t have done it without my supportive mom and dad who took my daughter for 24 straight days so I could travel, for my boyfriend who convinced me every single day that I was OVER it to not back down and not drop out, our nanny back home who watched our home and 3 dogs for 24 days, and of course my amazing mentors at TEP who coached me every step of the way!  I am eternally grateful to every single one of you who was a part of me accomplishing this and showed me exactly what I am capable of achieving.
✨
After my graduation, my sweet man @vantrinidad surprised me by taking me to Rodeo Drive to pickup a new Louis bag, wallet, and keychain to commemorate the accomplishment.  So grateful.  I honestly think I was so much in a daze that I didn’t even know what was happening.  Between the sleep deprivation and needing an emergency root canal in the middle of my trip, I was soooooo delirious. 😂😂😂 But he flew down the last two days of my program to push me over the finish line, and drive my car all the way back home so I could relax finally.  Whenever I look at this handbag daily, it’s not just a handbag, it’s something that was gifted to me for the blood, sweat and tears that I put into this goal for FIVE YEARS, and finally finished it❣️Thank you baby ❤️
✨
